1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:02,210
[Espina] <i>I'm tired of pretending.</i>

2
00:00:02,293 --> 00:00:03,795
I'm tired of lying.

3
00:00:03,878 --> 00:00:05,672
But I do it every day.

4
00:00:05,755 --> 00:00:08,591
Especially now that Marcus
has become my friend.

5
00:00:08,675 --> 00:00:11,177
[Espina] <i>But our mission</i>
<i>with Mustapha isn't over yet.</i>

6
00:00:11,261 --> 00:00:14,264
<i>And justice hasn't yet been served</i>
<i>for my neighbors.</i>

7
00:00:14,347 --> 00:00:15,807
<i>I have to finish this.</i>

8
00:00:15,890 --> 00:00:18,309
[Lara] <i>I'm curious just how you</i>
<i>and Agent Reyes managed to get along.</i>

9
00:00:18,393 --> 00:00:20,603
And now he entrusted
Task Force Alpha to you.

10
00:00:20,687 --> 00:00:22,480
We've gotten to know each other better.

11
00:00:22,564 --> 00:00:23,732
[Espina] <i>I hope the same happens with us.</i>

12
00:00:23,815 --> 00:00:24,858
I'm not your enemy.

13
00:00:24,941 --> 00:00:27,736
[Espina] <i>But there are enemies</i>
<i>all around us.</i>

14
00:00:27,819 --> 00:00:32,657
<i>You, Lara, are my way of finding</i>
<i>the answers to my questions.</i>

15
00:00:32,741 --> 00:00:35,952
[Manuel] <i>We will consolidate</i>
<i>the resources of the police.</i>

16
00:00:36,036 --> 00:00:38,705
[in English] They won't even know
what's coming.

17
00:00:38,788 --> 00:00:41,249
The fleet schedule of this company

18
00:00:41,332 --> 00:00:42,667
is still going 'til now.

19
00:00:42,751 --> 00:00:45,086
[Jalil] <i>Agent Angeles, I need your help.</i>

20
00:00:45,170 --> 00:00:46,755
[Lara] They're on the way
to an abandoned building

21
00:00:46,838 --> 00:00:48,631
at the corner of Kalantiaw
and Tasaday Street.

22
00:00:48,715 --> 00:00:50,258
[Lara, in English] <i>That's where</i>
<i>the target is going.</i>

23
00:00:50,341 --> 00:00:51,926
[in English] <i>You have three minutes.</i>

24
00:00:52,010 --> 00:00:53,636
- [Felix] Get out!
- [officer] Get out of the car!

25
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:58,183
[Ahmad] <i>Every move</i>
<i>is too carefully planned. Too flawless.</i>

26
00:00:58,266 --> 00:00:59,100
<i>This means…</i>

27
00:00:59,184 --> 00:01:02,937
<i>that a single hand</i>
<i>is directing all of you.</i>

28
00:01:03,021 --> 00:01:07,942
Which one of you is the mastermind
behind all this?

29
00:01:08,026 --> 00:01:11,362
[Marcus] <i>The generals will announce</i>
<i>their decision tomorrow, Ma.</i>

30
00:01:11,446 --> 00:01:14,449
<i>I don't know how to feel</i>
<i>if I'm removed from service.</i>

31
00:01:14,532 --> 00:01:17,786
<i>I feel like Gabriel</i>
<i>will be disappointed in me.</i>

32
00:01:17,869 --> 00:01:19,996
[Teresa] <i>Believe in yourself.</i>

33
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:22,707
<i>Don't let those bastards bring you down.</i>

34
00:01:22,791 --> 00:01:25,210
May Allah guide you.

35
00:01:25,293 --> 00:01:28,630
PREVIOUSLY

36
00:01:28,713 --> 00:01:35,678
[mysterious theme music playing]

37
00:01:39,307 --> 00:01:44,062
BLOOD VS DUTY

38
00:01:44,145 --> 00:01:46,648
[suspenseful music playing]

39
00:01:46,731 --> 00:01:48,817
[Villanueva] Agent Reyes.

40
00:01:51,736 --> 00:01:53,613
We will now announce our judgment.

41
00:01:54,489 --> 00:01:56,991
[in English] Please. Have a seat.

42
00:01:59,369 --> 00:02:01,246
[in English] I prefer to stand, sir.

43
00:02:01,329 --> 00:02:02,705
[scoffs]

44
00:02:03,289 --> 00:02:04,749
[in English] Very well.

45
00:02:05,542 --> 00:02:07,335
Is Azuelo here yet?

46
00:02:07,418 --> 00:02:08,878
He's on his way, sir.

47
00:02:13,758 --> 00:02:15,176
[Villanueva, in English] Oh, good!

48
00:02:15,260 --> 00:02:16,511
[in English] You're here.

49
00:02:18,096 --> 00:02:19,597
[in English] We can start.

50
00:02:20,849 --> 00:02:22,433
Sir, before we begin…

51
00:02:23,393 --> 00:02:25,770
may I say something?

52
00:02:27,897 --> 00:02:31,568
[sighs] What is it this time,
Director Azuelo?

53
00:02:31,651 --> 00:02:33,736
[in English] We've already
made a decision!

54
00:02:33,820 --> 00:02:36,156
What is it, Azuelo?

55
00:02:36,239 --> 00:02:41,828
[suspenseful music continues]

56
00:02:44,414 --> 00:02:45,623
At first,

57
00:02:47,458 --> 00:02:49,669
I chose to stay silent

58
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:54,549
because I didn't want
to compromise the mission.

59
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:56,759
But now,

60
00:02:56,843 --> 00:02:59,387
I cannot sacrifice

61
00:02:59,470 --> 00:03:02,056
one of my men just because
of one operation.

62
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:07,645
All of our hard work will go to waste

63
00:03:07,729 --> 00:03:14,360
if I simply let one of my best agents go.

64
00:03:14,444 --> 00:03:16,487
NATIONAL LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENCY

65
00:03:16,571 --> 00:03:21,618
Agent Marcus Reyes hid Datu Rathman

66
00:03:21,701 --> 00:03:24,370
- under my strict supervision.
- [dramatic stinging]

67
00:03:25,997 --> 00:03:29,876
[in English] Under
my explicit instructions.

68
00:03:29,959 --> 00:03:33,838
[in English] He was acting
on a clandestine operation

69
00:03:33,922 --> 00:03:36,132
officially sanctioned by the SID.

70
00:03:36,216 --> 00:03:38,259
So, legally speaking, sir,

71
00:03:38,843 --> 00:03:43,598
you can't remove Agent Reyes from service.

72
00:03:43,681 --> 00:03:45,308
[in English] That's preposterous!

73
00:03:46,017 --> 00:03:47,143
[in English] You're making this up!

74
00:03:47,936 --> 00:03:50,230
I'm telling the truth.

75
00:03:50,813 --> 00:03:53,233
And you're not part
of the mission anyway, right?

76
00:03:53,316 --> 00:03:55,902
Why? Why were we kept in the dark?!

77
00:03:55,985 --> 00:03:58,947
Because we can't trust anyone!

78
00:04:00,531 --> 00:04:03,743
Datu Rahman's life is in danger.

79
00:04:03,826 --> 00:04:07,288
We can't just let anyone take him

80
00:04:07,372 --> 00:04:10,416
because he's going to get killed!

81
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:12,710
Because he is our key witness

82
00:04:12,794 --> 00:04:17,465
to find out who is behind all of this!

83
00:04:18,049 --> 00:04:19,759
Which is why we kept him.

84
00:04:20,593 --> 00:04:23,513
That's why I'm telling all of you,

85
00:04:23,596 --> 00:04:28,351
this is an official mission of the SID.

86
00:04:28,434 --> 00:04:33,314
[in English] Agent Reyes was operating
under my command!

87
00:04:34,274 --> 00:04:36,442
So if anyone
has to be responsible for this,

88
00:04:37,819 --> 00:04:39,779
it would be none other than me!

89
00:04:41,406 --> 00:04:43,825
So if you're going to fire Agent Reyes,

90
00:04:45,076 --> 00:04:46,536
you should fire me too.

91
00:04:46,619 --> 00:04:52,041
- [music intensifies]
- [dramatic stinging]

92
00:05:03,219 --> 00:05:05,013
[Espina] We are arresting you
for violating

93
00:05:05,096 --> 00:05:08,266
the Comprehensive Firearms
and Ammunition Regulation Act.

94
00:05:08,349 --> 00:05:09,517
Take them away.

95
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:10,435
‪[dramatic stinging]

96
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:17,525
[Madrigal] Your mission
is important to our cause.

97
00:05:17,608 --> 00:05:19,068
But don't worry.

98
00:05:19,152 --> 00:05:21,237
The generals haven't announced
their decision yet,

99
00:05:21,321 --> 00:05:23,114
but we've already won.

100
00:05:23,197 --> 00:05:25,491
We already have the power.

101
00:05:26,409 --> 00:05:27,702
Gentlemen.

102
00:05:27,785 --> 00:05:31,122
Your sacrifices won't be in vain.

103
00:05:31,205 --> 00:05:33,875
[stirring music playing]

104
00:05:33,958 --> 00:05:35,835
[in English] Easy now.

105
00:05:44,135 --> 00:05:45,261
[radio beeps]

106
00:05:45,344 --> 00:05:47,764
[in English] Base. This is Alpha One.
Target secured.

107
00:05:47,847 --> 00:05:49,724
[in English] Good job, Major Espina.

108
00:05:52,935 --> 00:05:54,145
Good job, everyone.

109
00:06:04,739 --> 00:06:05,698
[thuds]

110
00:06:08,076 --> 00:06:12,997
[stirring music continues]

111
00:06:20,296 --> 00:06:22,256
[objects rustling]

112
00:06:42,110 --> 00:06:43,194
Reyes, you bastard.

113
00:06:44,237 --> 00:06:47,365
Don't ever do that to me again!

114
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:50,576
[in English] Goddammit!

115
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:52,495
Sir, thank you, sir.

116
00:06:54,622 --> 00:06:55,915
[in English] Carry on.

117
00:07:04,674 --> 00:07:09,762
SPECIAL INVESTIGATIONS DIVISION

118
00:07:11,681 --> 00:07:15,977
[stirring music continues]

119
00:07:31,993 --> 00:07:34,579
[Marcus] <i>I thought I'd never visit</i>
<i>this room again.</i>

120
00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:40,877
<i>I thought I'd never be able</i>
<i>to finish my mission, Gabriel.</i>

121
00:07:42,795 --> 00:07:44,046
We took this entrance

122
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:45,715
because the press is gathered out front.

123
00:07:45,798 --> 00:07:47,300
We'll get mobbed.

124
00:07:47,383 --> 00:07:48,301
Yeah, it's too shameful.

125
00:07:48,384 --> 00:07:50,803
To think our fellow officers
are behind this!

126
00:07:53,681 --> 00:07:55,016
Angeles.

127
00:07:55,099 --> 00:07:57,018
[in English] Congratulations, team.

128
00:07:58,853 --> 00:08:00,229
Yulo!

129
00:08:00,938 --> 00:08:02,064
Valdez!

130
00:08:02,565 --> 00:08:05,443
It just had to be you two, goddammit!

131
00:08:07,069 --> 00:08:08,696
[in English] Congratulations,
Major Espina,

132
00:08:09,363 --> 00:08:10,573
Agent Angeles.

133
00:08:10,656 --> 00:08:13,326
[in English] And congratulations,
Task Force Alpha.

134
00:08:14,494 --> 00:08:16,120
[in English] Mission accomplished!

135
00:08:16,204 --> 00:08:18,039
Thank you, sirs.

136
00:08:18,623 --> 00:08:19,999
Well, then.

137
00:08:20,082 --> 00:08:23,711
Book them and throw them
in their holding cell!

138
00:08:23,794 --> 00:08:24,962
[in English] Move!

139
00:08:25,046 --> 00:08:31,594
[tense music playing]

140
00:08:31,677 --> 00:08:32,803
[Azuelo] General.

141
00:08:50,696 --> 00:08:51,989
Sir Marcus?

142
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:55,076
Brother!

143
00:08:55,743 --> 00:08:56,869
[Marcus clears throat]

144
00:08:56,953 --> 00:08:58,204
How did it go?

145
00:09:00,122 --> 00:09:01,707
Are you here to say goodbye, sir?

146
00:09:02,917 --> 00:09:03,834
Come on, sir.

147
00:09:03,918 --> 00:09:05,670
We won't let that happen.

148
00:09:05,753 --> 00:09:07,505
- [somber music playing]
- [soft chuckle]

149
00:09:07,588 --> 00:09:09,131
You guys are doing too much.

150
00:09:09,715 --> 00:09:11,634
My suspension has been lifted,

151
00:09:11,717 --> 00:09:13,469
and they dropped the case against me.

152
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:15,012
[Liam applauding] Hell yeah!

153
00:09:15,096 --> 00:09:16,514
[uplifting music playing]

154
00:09:17,348 --> 00:09:18,558
Congrats, sir.

155
00:09:18,641 --> 00:09:20,226
Man! You had us there!

156
00:09:21,143 --> 00:09:23,020
[Ryan] He just had to give us
a little scare!

157
00:09:23,104 --> 00:09:24,981
[in English] Welcome back, Sir Marcus.

158
00:09:25,064 --> 00:09:28,609
Does this mean you'll be able
to join our operations again?

159
00:09:28,693 --> 00:09:29,819
Rodriguez!

160
00:09:31,821 --> 00:09:33,698
Do you want to get rid of me that badly?

161
00:09:33,781 --> 00:09:34,699
[chuckles nervously]

162
00:09:34,782 --> 00:09:36,117
Not at all, sir!

163
00:09:36,701 --> 00:09:38,828
[laughing]

164
00:09:38,911 --> 00:09:42,123
["Maninindigan" by Marko Rudio playing]

165
00:09:42,206 --> 00:09:43,708
[Marcus] Major.

166
00:09:43,791 --> 00:09:45,418
Agent Reyes.

167
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:49,672
Welcome back.

168
00:09:50,798 --> 00:09:52,091
Major Espina.

169
00:09:52,925 --> 00:09:55,011
I heard it was a mission accomplished.

170
00:09:55,803 --> 00:09:57,221
[in English] Congratulations.

171
00:09:59,974 --> 00:10:01,350
Thank you.

172
00:10:02,393 --> 00:10:04,145
Well, it looks like…

173
00:10:04,895 --> 00:10:08,357
I'll be taking back
Task Force Alpha from you.

174
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:10,318
It's all good.
I actually prefer it that way.

175
00:10:11,152 --> 00:10:14,947
Task Force Alpha wouldn't be
the same without you.

176
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:19,118
Did they give you a hard time?

177
00:10:19,201 --> 00:10:20,870
[Liam] Sir, us? No way.

178
00:10:20,953 --> 00:10:22,622
We were on our best behavior.

179
00:10:23,956 --> 00:10:25,458
[Felix] Sir Marcus.

180
00:10:26,417 --> 00:10:27,793
[in English] Congratulations.

181
00:10:28,461 --> 00:10:29,962
You're solid, man.

182
00:10:30,046 --> 00:10:31,088
[sniffles]

183
00:10:31,172 --> 00:10:32,298
[unsettling music playing]

184
00:10:32,381 --> 00:10:34,175
You know, I've never had…

185
00:10:36,093 --> 00:10:37,887
any doubts about you.

186
00:10:37,970 --> 00:10:39,889
[clicks tongue, chuckles]

187
00:10:43,267 --> 00:10:44,393
Right?

188
00:10:45,394 --> 00:10:46,228
‪[music intensifies]

189
00:10:50,107 --> 00:10:51,442
You're the man.

190
00:10:54,779 --> 00:10:55,905
[Liam] Congrats, sir!

191
00:10:55,988 --> 00:10:57,531
[team cheering]

192
00:10:57,615 --> 00:10:59,241
- [applause]
- [Liam grunts]

193
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:01,494
- You're my idol, Sir Marcus!
- [Liam] Yes, sir! That's right!

194
00:11:02,119 --> 00:11:03,996
[Liam] Congratulations, sir!

195
00:11:04,872 --> 00:11:05,956
A big round of applause, everyone!

196
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:07,667
- Sir Marcus!
- [officer] Whoo!

197
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:14,465
[Liam] Sir Marcus! Sir Marcus!
Sir Marcus! Sir Marcus!

198
00:11:15,049 --> 00:11:16,926
Sir, we're so excited to…

199
00:11:17,009 --> 00:11:18,386
[music concludes]

200
00:11:20,262 --> 00:11:21,722
Agent Angeles.

201
00:11:23,265 --> 00:11:24,308
How are you?

202
00:11:24,392 --> 00:11:25,559
Is everything okay?

203
00:11:26,435 --> 00:11:27,978
Why? What do you care?

204
00:11:28,479 --> 00:11:31,816
Oh, I just noticed that you've
been distant from everyone,

205
00:11:31,899 --> 00:11:33,234
- even from your colleagues.
- [scoffs]

206
00:11:33,317 --> 00:11:35,152
And so what?

207
00:11:36,737 --> 00:11:37,863
Are we close?

208
00:11:37,947 --> 00:11:40,741
Is this part of your mission,
or are you spying on me?

209
00:11:40,825 --> 00:11:41,826
[Espina] No, no.

210
00:11:41,909 --> 00:11:44,203
But it's my mission to get to know you.

211
00:11:44,286 --> 00:11:46,205
Besides, I just wanted to ask you.

212
00:11:46,288 --> 00:11:48,374
Honestly, I think…

213
00:11:49,291 --> 00:11:51,168
no one ever asks how you're doing.

214
00:11:51,252 --> 00:11:52,253
[Lara scoffs]

215
00:11:52,336 --> 00:11:53,838
[in English] Excuse me?

216
00:11:53,921 --> 00:11:56,882
Can you please leave me alone?

217
00:11:56,966 --> 00:11:58,801
You don't need to check up on me.

218
00:11:58,884 --> 00:11:59,802
[somber music playing]

219
00:11:59,885 --> 00:12:02,054
You're good at pretending you're okay.

220
00:12:03,097 --> 00:12:05,182
But your eyes tell the truth.

221
00:12:06,016 --> 00:12:07,268
I know we're not friends,

222
00:12:07,351 --> 00:12:09,645
but if you ever need someone to talk to…

223
00:12:10,688 --> 00:12:11,856
I'm here.

224
00:12:13,023 --> 00:12:14,150
Agent Angeles.

225
00:12:23,325 --> 00:12:28,998
[somber music continues]

226
00:12:33,878 --> 00:12:36,172
[traffic noise]

227
00:12:37,298 --> 00:12:39,175
- Hello, Doctor.
- Hello.

228
00:12:39,258 --> 00:12:41,510
- Good morning, Doctor.
- [in English] Morning.

229
00:12:41,594 --> 00:12:43,053
You seem to be in a good mood.

230
00:12:43,137 --> 00:12:44,597
Is there any good news?

231
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:45,890
Marcus called.

232
00:12:45,973 --> 00:12:47,683
The charges against him
have been dismissed.

233
00:12:47,766 --> 00:12:49,477
His suspension has also been lifted.

234
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:52,646
That's amazing news, Doctor.

235
00:12:52,730 --> 00:12:56,775
At least now he can really
carry out his duties well.

236
00:12:56,859 --> 00:12:59,445
I know. Thank God.

237
00:12:59,528 --> 00:13:01,489
[gentle music playing]

238
00:13:01,572 --> 00:13:03,157
How sweet of you.

239
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:04,533
- Supportive, huh?
- [whispers] Hey.

240
00:13:04,617 --> 00:13:05,576
If she hears you…

241
00:13:05,659 --> 00:13:06,619
Our friendship's done.

242
00:13:07,328 --> 00:13:08,704
I'll head to the ER, alright?

243
00:13:08,787 --> 00:13:11,790
I want to finish work early,
so I can prepare food at home.

244
00:13:11,874 --> 00:13:14,293
I'm expecting both of you.
We're going to celebrate.

245
00:13:14,376 --> 00:13:17,713
I also told Marcus
to invite the whole team.

246
00:13:17,796 --> 00:13:20,257
Sure thing, Doctor.
Jamilah and I will be there.

247
00:13:20,341 --> 00:13:21,258
- Alright, then.
- [chuckles awkwardly]

248
00:13:22,551 --> 00:13:24,136
Whatever. You're on your own now.

249
00:13:25,179 --> 00:13:27,139
Come here, you little busybody.

250
00:13:27,223 --> 00:13:28,516
- Oh my God!
- Ouch…

251
00:13:28,599 --> 00:13:31,143
You're focusing on everything
but work, huh?

252
00:13:31,227 --> 00:13:36,148
[music becomes ominous]

253
00:13:37,024 --> 00:13:40,110
[morose music playing]

254
00:13:40,194 --> 00:13:41,737
[Espina] <i>Honestly, I think</i>

255
00:13:42,613 --> 00:13:45,074
<i>no one ever asks how you're doing.</i>

256
00:13:54,208 --> 00:13:56,460
<i>You're good at pretending you're okay.</i>

257
00:13:56,544 --> 00:13:58,671
<i>But your eyes tell the truth.</i>

258
00:13:58,754 --> 00:14:01,757
[morose music continues]

259
00:14:15,229 --> 00:14:16,814
[laughter]

260
00:14:16,897 --> 00:14:19,191
I'm counting on seeing you there, okay?

261
00:14:19,275 --> 00:14:20,901
My mother's been cooking all day,

262
00:14:20,985 --> 00:14:22,278
so the whole team should come.

263
00:14:22,361 --> 00:14:23,779
Absolutely, buddy. We'll be there.

264
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:25,573
Count us in. I'll make sure they show up.

265
00:14:25,656 --> 00:14:29,034
[Liam] Sir, if there's food,
you can bet I'll come.

266
00:14:29,118 --> 00:14:31,161
[Ryan] That's a given, sir. I'm in, too.

267
00:14:31,245 --> 00:14:32,246
[Eve, in English] See you, sir.

268
00:14:32,329 --> 00:14:33,455
[Marcus, in English] Good.

269
00:14:33,539 --> 00:14:35,082
How about you? Be sure to come.

270
00:14:35,165 --> 00:14:37,126
You're now my mother's favorite.

271
00:14:37,918 --> 00:14:39,044
I'll be there.

272
00:14:39,128 --> 00:14:40,671
Do you promise, bro?

273
00:14:41,338 --> 00:14:43,048
I promise, bro.

274
00:14:44,758 --> 00:14:46,218
[somber music playing]

275
00:14:46,302 --> 00:14:47,720
[Marcus] Lara.

276
00:14:48,345 --> 00:14:50,222
Come by the house later.

277
00:14:50,306 --> 00:14:52,725
My mother's preparing a simple dinner.

278
00:14:52,808 --> 00:14:55,686
Oh. Just tell Miss Teresa
I'll pass for now.

279
00:14:55,769 --> 00:14:57,354
I have a lot of work to do. Thank you.

280
00:14:57,438 --> 00:14:59,982
[Espina] Are you sure? It'll be fun.

281
00:15:00,065 --> 00:15:01,650
A chance for everyone to bond.

282
00:15:02,776 --> 00:15:04,653
[in English] Next time.
I have a lot to do.

283
00:15:04,737 --> 00:15:07,031
- [in English] Enjoy
- [Liam] Alright, ma'am.

284
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:09,992
Felix. Are you going?

285
00:15:10,075 --> 00:15:11,201
Of course, sir. I wouldn't miss it.

286
00:15:11,285 --> 00:15:12,286
[Marcus] Very good.

287
00:15:12,369 --> 00:15:13,287
[phone ringing]

288
00:15:13,370 --> 00:15:14,246
- That's what I like.
- Oh!

289
00:15:14,330 --> 00:15:15,581
[in English] Excuse me, sir.

290
00:15:15,664 --> 00:15:17,291
Wait a minute. I'll just answer it.

291
00:15:17,374 --> 00:15:19,376
[somber music continues]

292
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:22,296
[Marcus] After this,
we'll go straight there.

293
00:15:23,047 --> 00:15:25,299
Well, any updates?

294
00:15:25,382 --> 00:15:27,593
[goon] <i>Sir, I have the name of the woman</i>

295
00:15:27,676 --> 00:15:29,261
<i>you want me to spy on.</i>

296
00:15:29,762 --> 00:15:31,430
<i>Jamilah Abubakar.</i>

297
00:15:32,014 --> 00:15:33,307
Alright, thank you.

298
00:15:33,390 --> 00:15:35,726
[indistinct chattering]

299
00:15:35,809 --> 00:15:37,853
- [clears throat] Sir!
- [officer] Now, that's the real…

300
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:40,522
Sorry. I'm taking a rain check.

301
00:15:41,023 --> 00:15:41,982
There's an emergency.

302
00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:44,985
But I'll make it up
to you next time, okay?

303
00:15:45,069 --> 00:15:45,986
Enjoy.

304
00:15:46,070 --> 00:15:47,655
- What a bummer.
- Alright, next time then.

305
00:15:47,738 --> 00:15:48,989
Take care.

306
00:15:50,157 --> 00:15:55,746
[suspenseful music playing]

307
00:16:00,668 --> 00:16:04,630
Your goal is to protect
every corner of this place.

308
00:16:04,713 --> 00:16:05,965
[pensive music playing]

309
00:16:06,048 --> 00:16:09,093
No threat or explosion
must be allowed to slip through.

310
00:16:09,176 --> 00:16:11,971
[in English] This place has to be
absolutely secured.

311
00:16:12,054 --> 00:16:13,013
Is that clear?

312
00:16:13,097 --> 00:16:14,264
[all, in unison] Yes, sir!

313
00:16:20,312 --> 00:16:23,941
[pensive music continues]

314
00:16:26,026 --> 00:16:27,486
[in English] Dismissed!

315
00:16:34,451 --> 00:16:35,703
General.

316
00:16:37,037 --> 00:16:38,998
Our agents have been discovered.

317
00:16:40,332 --> 00:16:41,333
[in English] Good.

318
00:16:41,417 --> 00:16:45,671
[in English] Now we can fully
control the narrative.

319
00:16:45,754 --> 00:16:48,340
We'll just have to get them

320
00:16:48,424 --> 00:16:51,385
when they least expect it.

321
00:16:51,468 --> 00:16:54,304
[snickers]

322
00:16:54,388 --> 00:16:58,809
[sinister music playing]

323
00:16:58,892 --> 00:17:03,022
NO PARKING!!

324
00:17:03,105 --> 00:17:06,275
[somber music playing]

325
00:17:12,406 --> 00:17:13,490
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

326
00:17:13,574 --> 00:17:15,492
My name is Sitti.

327
00:17:15,576 --> 00:17:17,494
I'm new here.

328
00:17:17,578 --> 00:17:19,747
Can I play with you?

329
00:17:19,830 --> 00:17:21,206
What are you wearing on your head?

330
00:17:21,290 --> 00:17:22,791
Yeah, what's up with that thing?

331
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:24,460
Take it off, okay?

332
00:17:24,543 --> 00:17:26,128
Oh, this?

333
00:17:26,211 --> 00:17:28,005
I can't take this off.

334
00:17:28,088 --> 00:17:31,508
Then you can't play with us!

335
00:17:32,551 --> 00:17:34,595
Hey, no! No!

336
00:17:34,678 --> 00:17:37,222
Please, don't pull it!

337
00:17:37,306 --> 00:17:39,558
- Please!
- [girls giggling]

338
00:17:39,641 --> 00:17:41,810
Don't yank it, please!

339
00:17:41,894 --> 00:17:43,520
- That's enough!
- You're so mean!

340
00:17:43,604 --> 00:17:45,647
- You're so mean!
- Stop fighting!

341
00:17:45,731 --> 00:17:47,608
Sitti, what happened?

342
00:17:47,691 --> 00:17:50,569
Nazia, they started it!

343
00:17:50,652 --> 00:17:53,280
They were tugging at my hijab!

344
00:17:53,363 --> 00:17:55,157
[somber music continues]

345
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:56,825
Girls…

346
00:17:57,326 --> 00:18:00,204
Hijab is the name of the fabric
Sitti and I are wearing.

347
00:18:00,871 --> 00:18:03,332
In our Muslim culture and religion,

348
00:18:03,415 --> 00:18:07,461
we practice it as a sign of our respect

349
00:18:07,544 --> 00:18:10,339
and loyalty to our beliefs.

350
00:18:10,422 --> 00:18:13,050
So it can't just be removed.

351
00:18:13,133 --> 00:18:14,718
Especially by other people.

352
00:18:14,802 --> 00:18:18,430
No matter how different we look
or what we believe,

353
00:18:18,514 --> 00:18:22,392
it's important that we respect each other.

354
00:18:22,476 --> 00:18:23,894
Is that okay?

355
00:18:23,977 --> 00:18:26,105
- Yes, we're sorry.
- Yes, we're sorry.

356
00:18:26,188 --> 00:18:28,816
- They just apologized.
- I'm sorry, kid.

357
00:18:28,899 --> 00:18:32,945
[somber music continues]

358
00:18:34,321 --> 00:18:36,240
Don't fight anymore, okay?

359
00:18:36,323 --> 00:18:37,866
You can be friends.

360
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:40,327
I'm Sitti, by the way.

361
00:18:40,410 --> 00:18:42,788
Do you want to play with us?
I can teach you.

362
00:18:42,871 --> 00:18:43,997
- Come on.
- Okay.

363
00:18:44,081 --> 00:18:45,332
Let's go.

364
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:47,793
Stand here.

365
00:18:47,876 --> 00:18:50,921
Do you see that rock?
You just need to hop…

366
00:18:53,715 --> 00:18:54,633
[Jamilah] Gracia…

367
00:18:54,716 --> 00:18:56,468
[Teresa] I'll get going now.

368
00:18:56,552 --> 00:18:58,011
I'll see you at home.

369
00:18:58,095 --> 00:18:59,805
Have a safe trip, alright?

370
00:18:59,888 --> 00:19:01,014
Yes, Doctor.

371
00:19:01,098 --> 00:19:03,684
We'll join you
once our shift is over. Thank you.

372
00:19:03,767 --> 00:19:05,310
If you ever have trouble getting a ride,

373
00:19:05,394 --> 00:19:06,478
just text me right away.

374
00:19:06,562 --> 00:19:08,355
I can ask Marcus to pick you up.

375
00:19:08,438 --> 00:19:09,565
- Oh…
- D-Doctor!

376
00:19:09,648 --> 00:19:11,358
- She'd really like that--
- Oh, that's not true!

377
00:19:11,441 --> 00:19:13,152
We'll find a way, Doctor.

378
00:19:13,235 --> 00:19:14,778
- Alright, then.
- Okay, take care.

379
00:19:14,862 --> 00:19:17,030
- Thanks. See you!
- You just won't stop, huh?

380
00:19:17,739 --> 00:19:18,824
[Gracia] Wait!

381
00:19:19,449 --> 00:19:22,452
[Peter] Come here!
Girl, you're so unbelievable!

382
00:19:22,536 --> 00:19:24,413
My goodness! You just can't help…

383
00:19:24,496 --> 00:19:26,582
NATIONAL LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENCY

384
00:19:26,665 --> 00:19:28,458
It's strange, sir,
that you haven't presented

385
00:19:28,542 --> 00:19:31,170
Major Yulo and Captain Valdez
to the press yet.

386
00:19:31,253 --> 00:19:34,423
This arrest is very sensitive.

387
00:19:35,007 --> 00:19:38,010
Our fellow officers
and high-ranking officials

388
00:19:38,093 --> 00:19:40,262
are the real culprits.

389
00:19:40,345 --> 00:19:44,641
We must first make sure
what those two really know

390
00:19:44,725 --> 00:19:46,351
before we say something.

391
00:19:46,435 --> 00:19:48,687
[gloomy music continues]

392
00:19:48,770 --> 00:19:50,647
The interrogations start tomorrow.

393
00:19:50,731 --> 00:19:54,359
I need you there, Major Espina
and Agent Reyes.

394
00:19:54,443 --> 00:19:55,777
[both, in English] Yes, sir.

395
00:19:55,861 --> 00:19:56,862
[in English] Good.

396
00:19:57,446 --> 00:19:58,488
I have to go now.

397
00:19:58,572 --> 00:20:00,741
My family's waiting for me at home.

398
00:20:01,366 --> 00:20:03,410
- [in English] Enjoy the rest of the night.
- [in English] Thank you, sir.

399
00:20:03,493 --> 00:20:04,828
- Sir.
- [in English] Thank you, sir.

400
00:20:06,038 --> 00:20:07,331
[Azuelo, in English] Thank you.

401
00:20:07,414 --> 00:20:09,541
[gloomy music continues]

402
00:20:09,625 --> 00:20:11,627
- Bye-bye!
- Girl.

403
00:20:11,710 --> 00:20:15,088
Good thing your trip to Canada
didn't push through.

404
00:20:15,714 --> 00:20:16,924
Right?

405
00:20:17,007 --> 00:20:21,303
Well, sis, you know,
I still really prefer it here.

406
00:20:21,386 --> 00:20:24,014
- I don't think I could leave.
- [Jamilah giggles]

407
00:20:24,097 --> 00:20:25,182
This is crazy.

408
00:20:25,265 --> 00:20:27,726
Everything's such a mess, but it's fine.

409
00:20:27,809 --> 00:20:28,977
- But you know…
- Yeah?

410
00:20:29,061 --> 00:20:31,188
Something good also came out
of your almost leaving.

411
00:20:31,271 --> 00:20:33,398
- Huh?
- I got even closer to Gracia!

412
00:20:33,482 --> 00:20:35,984
- I see.
- Yes!

413
00:20:36,068 --> 00:20:37,861
You're so dramatic!

414
00:20:37,945 --> 00:20:40,364
Oh no, I hope we can get a ride soon.

415
00:20:40,447 --> 00:20:41,949
- I really don't want to be late, girl.
- [Peter mutters]

416
00:20:42,032 --> 00:20:43,867
- [Peter] Yeah.
- And I'm telling you,

417
00:20:43,951 --> 00:20:45,869
we should've just let Sir Marcus drive us.

418
00:20:45,953 --> 00:20:47,329
- It's her fault.
- No way.

419
00:20:47,412 --> 00:20:48,789
That's embarrassing.

420
00:20:48,872 --> 00:20:50,540
You're just excited to see your crush.

421
00:20:50,624 --> 00:20:52,626
- There it is.
- Oh, just me?

422
00:20:53,252 --> 00:20:55,170
- Huh?
- Girl, you too.

423
00:20:55,254 --> 00:20:56,421
- There it is.
- Girl…

424
00:20:56,505 --> 00:20:58,298
I don't have a crush on Dr. Teresa's son.

425
00:20:58,382 --> 00:20:59,549
Hmm, you denial frogs.

426
00:20:59,633 --> 00:21:01,176
- I really don't.
- Stop denying it.

427
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:02,970
- Let's hurry, we're going to be late.
- [Gracia mutters]

428
00:21:04,054 --> 00:21:05,305
[distant chattering]

429
00:21:05,389 --> 00:21:07,099
- [Sean] I can already smell it.
- Oh!

430
00:21:07,182 --> 00:21:08,809
- [Teresa] You’re here!
- Auntie, good evening.

431
00:21:08,892 --> 00:21:11,270
- [Teresa] Good evening!
- Wow, that looks so good.

432
00:21:11,353 --> 00:21:13,230
That's a lot. Did you cook my favorite?

433
00:21:13,313 --> 00:21:14,439
[Teresa] Of course.

434
00:21:14,523 --> 00:21:16,942
Sir Marcus rarely invites us.
Do you have the spring rolls?

435
00:21:17,025 --> 00:21:18,235
[Marcus] You know these guys, Ma.

436
00:21:18,318 --> 00:21:20,070
Sean and Usman.

437
00:21:20,153 --> 00:21:22,656
These are our new TFA members.

438
00:21:22,739 --> 00:21:27,119
- Liam, Andre, Eve…
- [soft greetings]

439
00:21:27,202 --> 00:21:28,870
- [Eve] Hi, Eve.
- And Ryan.

440
00:21:29,705 --> 00:21:31,039
[Teresa] Hi.

441
00:21:31,581 --> 00:21:33,417
Come on, sit down.

442
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:36,003
- Feel at home. Don't be shy.
- Thank you, Dr. Teresa.

443
00:21:36,086 --> 00:21:37,921
- This is amazing.
- Let's eat.

444
00:21:38,005 --> 00:21:40,132
- Good evening.
- [Liam] This is embarrassing.

445
00:21:40,215 --> 00:21:41,925
- How are you?
- [Teresa] Good evening.

446
00:21:42,009 --> 00:21:44,261
We're good, Allan. How about you?

447
00:21:44,344 --> 00:21:47,681
Oh, I cooked your and Marcus'
favorite vegetables.

448
00:21:47,764 --> 00:21:49,266
[Liam] That's so manly.

449
00:21:50,309 --> 00:21:53,395
Ma, I brought your new favorite.

450
00:21:55,063 --> 00:21:58,025
[Teresa giggles] Come on, Marcus.

451
00:21:58,108 --> 00:21:59,693
Come on, have a seat.

452
00:21:59,776 --> 00:22:01,069
Wait…

453
00:22:01,153 --> 00:22:03,280
- Have a seat.
- Okay.

454
00:22:03,363 --> 00:22:05,115
Is everyone here, son?

455
00:22:05,198 --> 00:22:07,826
Felix and Lara can't make it.

456
00:22:07,909 --> 00:22:09,953
Oh, that's too bad.

457
00:22:10,037 --> 00:22:13,957
So we're only missing Jamilah and Gracia.

458
00:22:14,583 --> 00:22:15,876
Jamilah is coming?

459
00:22:18,086 --> 00:22:19,463
And Gracia too?

460
00:22:19,546 --> 00:22:21,757
Yes, I invited them.

461
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:24,134
Maybe they're having trouble
getting a ride.

462
00:22:24,217 --> 00:22:25,343
It's rush hour.

463
00:22:25,427 --> 00:22:27,262
Son, why don't you go pick them up?

464
00:22:27,345 --> 00:22:28,722
Sure. Where are they?

465
00:22:29,598 --> 00:22:31,433
[Teresa] Wait, I'll call them.

466
00:22:34,019 --> 00:22:35,353
[Liam] Look at this guy.

467
00:22:36,021 --> 00:22:37,773
Remember when Sir Marcus scolded us?

468
00:22:37,856 --> 00:22:38,857
Reyes.

469
00:22:38,940 --> 00:22:41,234
If you want, I can pick them up.

470
00:22:41,943 --> 00:22:43,528
Stay here and help Dr. Teresa.

471
00:22:43,612 --> 00:22:45,530
- [Liam] Listen to Usman.
- I'll go.

472
00:22:45,614 --> 00:22:47,908
Bro, you're a guest here.

473
00:22:47,991 --> 00:22:49,785
Relax. I'll handle it.

474
00:22:50,410 --> 00:22:52,079
I'll go pick them up.

475
00:22:55,916 --> 00:22:58,376
They're still near the hospital area,

476
00:22:58,460 --> 00:23:00,504
but they haven't gotten a ride yet.

477
00:23:00,587 --> 00:23:02,172
Go pick them up, son.

478
00:23:02,255 --> 00:23:03,298
I've got it, Ma.

479
00:23:03,381 --> 00:23:04,591
I'll be quick.

480
00:23:04,674 --> 00:23:06,051
[Andre] Sir, I'll come with you.

481
00:23:06,802 --> 00:23:08,678
Sir, no. He's staying here.

482
00:23:08,762 --> 00:23:10,555
Just stay here. Come on.

483
00:23:10,639 --> 00:23:12,724
Just wait for Gracia.

484
00:23:12,808 --> 00:23:14,017
She'll come.

485
00:23:17,020 --> 00:23:18,105
Be careful.

486
00:23:18,980 --> 00:23:19,898
Just relax here.

487
00:23:21,817 --> 00:23:24,069
So, how are you guys? How's work?

488
00:23:24,152 --> 00:23:25,237
[Sean] We're good, Auntie.

489
00:23:25,320 --> 00:23:27,030
[Liam] Actually, it's better now,

490
00:23:27,114 --> 00:23:28,615
especially with your feast.

491
00:23:28,698 --> 00:23:30,742
I hope you enjoy the food.

492
00:23:30,826 --> 00:23:32,911
[Liam] Auntie, I already love it
just from the smell.

493
00:23:32,994 --> 00:23:34,663
I already told them
about your spring rolls.

494
00:23:34,746 --> 00:23:35,956
Of course.

495
00:23:36,039 --> 00:23:37,707
- Dr. Teresa called.
- What?

496
00:23:37,791 --> 00:23:40,085
Sir Marcus is coming to pick us up.

497
00:23:40,168 --> 00:23:41,711
- Oh my!
- Here we go.

498
00:23:41,795 --> 00:23:44,131
Okay, you know what to do, right?

499
00:23:44,214 --> 00:23:46,424
- When he arrives, sit in front.
- Huh?

500
00:23:46,508 --> 00:23:48,343
- Sit next to him.
- [Peter] You should, girl.

501
00:23:48,426 --> 00:23:49,719
- No way!
- [Peter] You're so dramatic!

502
00:23:49,803 --> 00:23:51,054
I'm sitting at the back with you guys.

503
00:23:51,138 --> 00:23:54,224
Girl, are you really making him
our personal driver?

504
00:23:54,307 --> 00:23:56,852
- I don't want to!
- [Peter] You're impossible!

505
00:23:56,935 --> 00:23:59,187
Fine, I don't care. I'm not doing it.

506
00:23:59,271 --> 00:24:00,730
- You sit in front if you want.
- Huh?

507
00:24:00,814 --> 00:24:04,568
[ominous music playing]

508
00:24:10,073 --> 00:24:14,119
I'll finally get my revenge
on you, Jalil Abubakar.

509
00:24:14,202 --> 00:24:16,830
[both grunting]

510
00:24:17,998 --> 00:24:19,249
[shouts]

511
00:24:20,959 --> 00:24:26,673
Now I'll use your sister
to force you out of hiding.

512
00:24:26,756 --> 00:24:28,133
Coward!

513
00:24:29,092 --> 00:24:30,343
[laughs maniacally]

514
00:24:30,427 --> 00:24:35,765
[ominous music continues]

515
00:24:37,726 --> 00:24:40,395
NEXT ON BLOOD VS DUTY

516
00:24:40,478 --> 00:24:43,190
Sir Marcus and Major Espina
used to fight a lot.

517
00:24:43,273 --> 00:24:46,401
What matters is they're on
the same side now, right?

518
00:24:46,484 --> 00:24:50,155
From what we see, they're like brothers.

519
00:24:50,238 --> 00:24:52,991
I don't even know anymore
if I'm doing the right thing.

520
00:24:53,074 --> 00:24:55,285
[Lara] <i>So many people</i>
<i>are getting dragged into this.</i>

521
00:24:55,368 --> 00:24:58,955
Whatever the General says,
that's what's right.

522
00:25:00,540 --> 00:25:03,668
[Azuelo] How do you operate
inside the NLEA?

523
00:25:03,752 --> 00:25:08,048
To protect the syndicate's transactions
from the inside.

524
00:25:08,131 --> 00:25:10,550
It's just business, sir. Money talks.

525
00:25:10,634 --> 00:25:13,803
What does Datu Rahman
have to do with all this?

526
00:25:19,935 --> 00:25:21,061
[Jamilah shrieks] No!

527
00:25:23,438 --> 00:25:25,857
[grunting]

528
00:25:25,941 --> 00:25:27,525
[man grunting]

529
00:25:28,526 --> 00:25:30,195
[Jamilah] Gracia!

530
00:25:30,278 --> 00:25:32,072
- [Gracia] Help!
- [car honks]

531
00:25:35,075 --> 00:25:39,913
BLOOD VS DUTY
